    <bioghist id="aspace_3aa9145b6f6e3cf229fbc505dfdab1a1">
      <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Founded in 1982, the Radical Philosophy Association (RPA) is an international organization whose mission is to oppose capitalism, racism, sexism, homophobia, disability discrimination, pollution, and authoritarianism by drawing upon a variety of radical traditions including phenomenology, Marxism, anarchism, post-structuralism, post-colonial theory and environmentalism. Its efforts center on conferences and publications. The RPA also publishes the journal Radical Philosophy Review.</p>
      <p>Robert A. Stone is a member of RPA and has taught philosophy at institutions including Long Island University in New York.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <processinfo id="aspace_419dcc5ed866cdbf06105af868717569">
      <head>Processing Note</head>
      <p>No original order was apparent upon receipt. Non-photographic materials were placed in acid-free folders. Photographs and slides have been kept in their original boxes and envelopes. All materials were placed in an acid-free box.</p>
    </processinfo>
    <arrangement id="aspace_20d96ce1e22782d68f0cd84dd02fc65e">
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The archivist imposed no order on this collection. Its original arrangement was maintained. The collection consists of one series.</p>
      <p>I. Radical Philosophy Association Images.</p>
    </arrangement>
    <custodhist id="aspace_355d9ad55fc816aad2072f59697341e3">
      <head>Custodial History</head>
      <p>The Alternative Press Center held these photographs and slides until 2009 when it donated them to the Tamiment Library/Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives. The Radical Philosophy Association allowed the Tamiment Library/Wagner Labor Archives to take possession of these items in 2009 and sent additional materials in 2010. These donations were split into two collections: The Radical Philosophy Association Images Collection (PHOTOS.272) and Radical Philosophy Association Records Collection (TAM.466).</p>
    </custodhist>
    <acqinfo id="aspace_642735c9a1f232417b043c40720345b0">
      <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
      <p>Donated by the Radical Philosophy Association, 2009. The accession numbers associated with this gift are 2012.055 and NPA.2009.014.</p>
    </acqinfo>
